== Description ==

The '''BIM Nudge''' tools are a set of commands that move (nudge) selected objects by small, configurable distances along the current [[Draft_SelectPlane|working plane]]. They are designed for quick, precise positioning of BIM elements using keyboard shortcuts.

The nudge distance can be set to "auto" mode, which automatically scales the nudge step based on the current view zoom level, or to a fixed value.

